Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
unsetPinConstraint(25.10)                            unsetPinConstraint(25.10)

Name
       unsetPinConstraint - Removes the constraints for a partition pin

Syntax
       unsetPinConstraint

       [-help]

       {[-global | -cell <cell_name> | -all_user ]

       [-global  |  -pin <pin_name_list> | -area {<x1 y1 x2 y2>} | -all_area |
       -side <side_names>]

       [-global | -layer ] [-global | -loc | -edge | -corner <corner_number>]

       [[-pin <pin_name_list> [-loc ] [-edge ]] |

       [-corner_to_pin_distance [-corner <corner_number>]]]

       [{-pin <pin_name_list> | -pinTemplate {<layer_id_or_name_list>}} -width
       ]

       [{-pin <pin_name_list> | -pinTemplate {<layer_id_or_name_list>}} -depth
       ]

       [[-layer       [-side       <side_names>]]        |        -pinTemplate
       {<layer_id_or_name_list>}]

       [-spacing [-area {x1 y1 x2 y2}]

       [-all_area ] [-side <side_names>]] }

       [-depth [-special_wire ]] [-all_user ]

       Removes  the  constraints for a partition pin. You can use this command
       after setting the pin's constraints with the setPinConstraint command.

Parameters
       -all_area
              Specifies that spacing constraints on all areas  should  be  re-
              moved.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -all_user
              Specifies  that all user specified constraints should be removed
              from all levels (-global, -cell, and -pin level).

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -area {<x1 y1 x2 y2>}
              Specifies that the area overlapping with partition for which the
              spacing constraints have been specified should be removed.

              Data_type: box, optional

       -cell <cell_name>
              Specifies the name of the cell (partition). The cell name is not
              required if the command is run on a top-level cell.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -corner <corner_number>
              Specifies the corner of the partition block.

              Data_type: int, optional

       -corner_to_pin_distance
              Specifies that the corner to pin distance  constraints should be
              removed.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -depth Specifies the pin depth related constraints should be removed.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -edge  Specifies that edge-related constraints should be removed.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -global
              Specifies to reset global constraints.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information  for  each  unsetPinConstraint  parameter. For a de-
              tailed description of the command and all of its parameters, use
              the man command:

              man unsetPinConstraint

       -layer Specifies that the layer-related constraints should be removed.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -loc   Specifies that the location-related constraints  should  be  re-
              moved.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -pin <pin_name_list>
              Specifies  the  name of the partition pin. You can use wildcards
              (*?) with this parameter.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -side <side> <_name>
              Specifies name of the side. Valid values are { N S E W } or  { L
              B T R } or all.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -spacing
              Specifies that the spacing-related  constraints  should  be  re-
              moved.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -special_wire
              Specifies  that the depth constraint that is honored for special
              wire pins by the partition command should be removed.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -pinTemplate {<layer_id_or_name_list> }
              Specifies the metal layers for the width and  depth  constraints
              at global level and cell level.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -width <width>
              Specifies  that  the pin width related constraints should be re-
              moved.

              Data_type: bool, optional

Example
              * The following command removes the spacing-  and  layer-related
                constraints for all partition pins in the partition sheet14.

                unsetPinConstraint sheet14 -pin * -layer -spacing

              *

                The following command removes all constraints on globals.

                unsetPinConstraint -global

              * The following command removes all constraints on all cells.

                unsetPinConstraint -cell *

              * The following command removes all constraints on all pins.

                unsetPinConstraint -cell * -pin *

              * The  following command removes all constraints on cells, pins,
                and globals.

                unsetPinConstraint -all_user

